Drone Scanner (DroneS can) - Database Migrations

Migration files for dronescan schema updates.

Naming Convention
-----------------
NNN_description.sql

Examples:
  001_add_scan_timestamp.sql
  002_add_proxy_type_column.sql
  003_create_scan_results_index.sql


Example Migration File
----------------------
ALTER TABLE scans ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS scan_timestamp TIMESTAMP;
CREATE INDEX IF NOT EXISTS idx_scans_timestamp ON scans(scan_timestamp);


Checking Applied Migrations
----------------------------
To see which migrations have been applied to the dronescan database:

  psql dronescan -c "SELECT file FROM gnuworld_migrations WHERE module='dronescan' ORDER BY applied_at;"


Automatic Migration Application
--------------------------------
Migrations are applied automatically when dronescan starts. Simply:

  1. Place your migration file in this directory
  2. Restart gnuworld
  3. The migration will be automatically detected and applied

The migration system will log each migration as it's applied.
If a migration fails, gnuworld will exit with an error message.


For detailed documentation, see ../../doc/README.migrations
